# ── Quartus build intermediates (regenerated by compilation) ──────────────────
src/fpga/db/
src/fpga/incremental_db/
src/fpga/output_files/
src/fpga/ap_core_assignment_defaults.qdf
src/fpga/c5_pin_model_dump.txt
*.qws
*.rpt
*.summary
*.smsg
*.jdi

# ── Build log ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
quartus_build.log

# ── Claude Code local tooling ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.claude/

# ── Python bytecode cache (regenerated whenever a *.py is imported) ────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Note: dist/ IS committed on purpose — it holds the built bitstream + JSON, so a
# checkout gives a deployable core (minus the ROM, which the user builds).

# ── ROMs / romsets: NEVER commit copyrighted ROM data. Users build ringking.rom
#    themselves via pack_rom.py from their own romset (ringking.zip + kingofb.zip). ─
*.rom
*.zip
*.hex
src/fpga/apf/build_id.mif
